# Modify Data Preparation to Process Manual Transcripts

To continue your project without being blocked by YouTube's API, we will transition Step 2 so that it ingests raw transcripts that you physically copy and paste from YouTube's desktop interface.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> After approving this plan, you will need to manually copy the transcripts from your top 10 videos on YouTube and save them as individual `.txt` files inside a new folder called `manual_transcripts/` in your workspace. 

## Proposed Changes

### Data Pipeline Update
I will modify `2_prepare_training_data.py` so it no longer looks for `channel_data.json` from the broken Step 1 script.

#### [MODIFY] 2_prepare_training_data.py
1. **Change Input Source**: Will add script logic to automatically scan a folder named `manual_transcripts/`. The script will read every `.txt` file you dump in there.
2. **Handle Raw UI Timestamps**: When you copy a transcript from the YouTube side panel, it includes raw timestamps like `0:02`, `14:32`, etc. I will update the `clean_text` function to automatically use Regular Expressions (Regex) to scrub these timestamps and extra whitespace out so the model only learns from the spoken words.
3. **Preserve Context & Chunking**: You mentioned 20-minute videos. To ensure the RAG/Fine-tuning model learns properly, we'll keep all the text but intelligently slice them into chunks of ~500-1000 characters so no data is dropped and full context is kept.

## Verification Plan
1. We will create a `manual_transcripts` folder.
2. I will write a dummy test `.txt` file representing a copied transcript.
3. We will run `2_prepare_training_data.py` and verify that the output cleanly formats it into `training_data.json` without timestamps.
